{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1e79e87-cbd7-4678-ada6-0066a4b8bb7c","content":"I can help point you in the right direction! The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them — so it won't apply here.\n\nFor **analyzing** a `.dmp` file, use one of these tools:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — cross-platform, SOS-based commands (`clrstack`, `pe`, `dumpheap`, etc.)\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows) — load with SOS extension for managed debugging\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS) — `dotnet-sos install`, then `lldb -c <file.dmp>`\n\n### Quick start with `dotnet-dump`:\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\nThen inside the interactive session:\n```\n> clrstack          # managed call stacks\n> pe                # print last exception\n> dumpheap -stat    # heap summary\n> setthread <id>    # switch threads\n```\n\nThe `pe` (print exception) command is usually the fastest way to find the crash root cause.\n\nWould you like help with any specific step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2178a618-353a-46f0-9c1b-94f22656d6aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill isn't appropriate here. Let me provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":385,"requestId":"7653:834FC:DD54BF:1055365:69FE93A4"},"id":"2af0ecdd-e7b8-451f-b191-4153e76eab97","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:53:51.292Z","parentId":"810e578c-9589-4780-ad4f-d01fe231fedb"}
